elco Platform**\n\nI'm deep in the TelecomVerse platform design now, formulating the page story around its orchestration of network telemetry and support workflows. I'm leveraging high-frequency carrier waves and a massive-scale network mesh as the visual metaphor. The layout strategy includes an enterprise hero section, an editorial narrative on cell load optimization, and an interactive network core dashboard for simulating a live optical transport layer. I'm also planning modules in a Bento Grid and a carousel for autonomous agents.\n\n\n**Orchestrating Telemetry Workflows**\n\nI'm now integrating an interactive network mode selector that provides real-time automated routing logs and technician ticket creation, particularly for `/platforms/telecomverse`. I've added a mobile-first responsive grid and horizontal carousel strategy. I'm also preparing related links to `/industries/telecom`, `/platforms/control-center`, and `/platforms/foundry`, along with a premium CTA for carrier scalability. I'm also planning to incorporate more of the autonomous agent modules, like Network Operations Copilot.\n\n\n**Integrating Lucide Icons**\n\nI'm now integrating `lucide-react` icons within the `/app/platforms/` pages, focusing on those already in use. I'm focusing on icons like `HardHat`, `Compass`, `Activity`, `ShieldAlert`, `Cpu`, and `Layers` to enrich the existing layouts with a visual refresh. I'm also planning motion reveals, beautifully rendered SVGs, and am making sure to import only the available lucide-react icons for consistency and performance. I'm making sure these pages use `lucide-react` directly. I'm expanding this into a comprehensive visual update, including `BentoGrid`, `BentoCard`, `Carousel`, `RelatedPagesGrid`, and a `PremiumCTA`.\n\nI'm making excellent headway on designing the initial layout. It's truly coming together, featuring the beautiful simulators, layout strategies, interactive consoles, metrics, lists of modules, and linked resources. The `/platforms/oremesh` page is shaping up, and I'm feeling excited about the narrative design.\n\nI'm now visualizing a rugged mesh network, with subterranean and surface connections, as a visual metaphor. I'm focusing the layout around this. The layout strategy includes a modern hero section with an interactive mesh graphic and sections detailing the \"Ruggedized Edge Mesh,\" modular operations, and operational resource agents. I'm particularly keen on designing an interactive SVG mesh network diagram or a low-bandwidth node configuration console, focusing on the gateways and remote site supervisor visual.\n\nI'm now honing the interactive features. I'm especially focused on a low-bandwidth node simulator for `/platforms/oremesh`, enabling users to \"ping\" subterranean nodes and observe edge routing delay. I'm also considering a fully responsive mobile strategy with clean margins and overflow handling. `/platforms/retailmesh` is up next with a focus on an omnichannel ingestion network.\n\nI'm now expanding the `/platforms/retailmesh` section, focusing on modern visuals. It's coming together well, with a \"Seamless Storefront Integration\" editorial narrative and an \"Omnichannel Hub Visualizer\" interactive dashboard. I'm building out a \"Bento grid\" for omnichannel capabilities, an \"Active Swarm Agent Cards\" carousel, and related links. I'm also planning an interactive console simulating POS log ingestion, alongside a mobile-optimized layout.\n\nI'm deep in the TelecomVerse platform design now, formulating the page story around its orchestration of network telemetry and support workflows. I'm leveraging high-frequency carrier waves and a massive-scale network mesh as the visual metaphor. The layout strategy includes an enterprise hero section, an editorial narrative on cell load optimization, and an interactive network core dashboard for simulating a live optical transport layer. I'm also planning modules in a Bento Grid and a carousel for autonomous agents.\n\nI'm now integrating an interactive network mode selector that provides real-time automated routing logs and technician ticket creation, particularly for `/platforms/telecomverse`. I've added a mobile-first responsive grid and horizontal carousel strategy. I'm also preparing related links to `/industries/telecom`, `/platforms/control-center`, and `/platforms/foundry`, along with a premium CTA for carrier scalability. I'm also planning to incorporate more of the autonomous agent modules, like Network Operations Copilot.\n\n\n**Prioritizing Safe Icon Choices**\n\nI'm now prioritizing the reliability of the `lucide-react` icons and ensuring that only the most dependable options or custom inline SVGs are chosen. I'm focusing on icons like `Activity`, `Cpu`, `Network`, `Server`, and `Database` for their universal appeal. I'm also preparing the design plans, specifically for `/platforms/oremesh`, focusing on a narrative of heavy-duty edge mesh for extraction operations and designing an interactive subterranean node simulator for users. I'm excited by this.\n\n\n\n**Simulating Real-Time Queries**\n\nI'm currently focused on building a dynamic live log generator to simulate queries over active edge nodes. I'm prioritizing `/platforms/oremesh`, focusing on a clean CSS grid mobile flow for the card carousel. I'm building `/app/platforms/oremesh/page.tsx` and leaving existing landing pages untouched. I'm also planning the new `/app/platforms/retailmesh/page.tsx` to center around an ingestion hub dashboard, focusing on a real-time unified view.\n\n\n**Building the Omni-Channel Visual**\n\nI'm presently building out `/app/platforms/retailmesh/page.tsx`, focusing on the Omni-Channel Ingestion Hub. I'm prioritizing the Bento grid to showcase core capabilities and a carousel of agent cards for store operations, merchandising intelligence, and customer experience. I'm also preparing related links and a premium CTA. I'm incorporating interactive toggle modes to simulate real-time log outputs, as well as optimizing the mobile responsive design for padding, text, and carousel cards. I am using the existing landing pages as a reference.\n\n\n**Orchestrating Telecom Dispatch**\n\nI'm presently building out `/app/platforms/telecomverse/page.tsx`, centering on the TelecomVerse Core. I'm prioritizing the hero title, narrative section for network operations support, and an interactive telecom network supervisor dashboard. I'm focusing on \"Congestion Reroute\", \"Technician Dispatch\", or \"Customer Ticket Triage\", complete with automated carrier actions, a Bento grid, and an Agent Cards Carousel. I'm planning related links and a premium CTA, focusing on the mobile design with vertical stacking and clean responsive grids. I'm using existing landing pages as a reference.\n\n\n**Updating the Platform Grid**\n\nI'm now focusing on the `/app/platforms/page.tsx` file, specifically line 42. I need to integrate direct links to our platform meshes, `/platforms/oremesh`, `/platforms/retailmesh`, and `/platforms/telecomverse`, into the existing grid cards. This update includes adding or upgrading those grid cards to include links to the detailed platform pages.\n\n\n**Linking the Platform Pages**\n\nI'm now integrating new platform links directly into the existing grid on `/app/platforms/page.tsx`, specifically adding cards for \"OREMesh Platform,\" \"RetailMesh Platform,\" and \"TelecomVerse Core.\" I'm planning to make sure these links are highly clickable and user-friendly, with clean routes and descriptions for all. This will streamline navigation significantly!\n\n\n**Optimizing Platform Imports**\n\nI'm now streamlining the import statements on `/app/platforms/page.tsx` for consistency and readability. I'm leveraging the index file to consolidate all necessary components from `@/components/inner-pages` into a single, concise import statement using the recommended ES6 destructuring style. I'm verifying that all the required components are accurately exported and imported.\n\n\n**Refactoring Imports for Readability**\n\nI'm presently refactoring the imports in `/app/platforms/page.tsx` using an index file for cleaner code. I've consolidated all necessary components from `@/components/inner-pages` into one streamlined import with ES6 destructuring, ensuring consistency and readability. I'm verifying that all the required components are accurately exported and imported.\n\n\n**Designing the OREMesh Visualization**\n\nI'm starting the visual design for the `/platforms/oremesh` page with a custom SVG mesh network diagram. It will depict a subterranean topology with \"Surface Gateway Layer,\" \"Sub-Surface Routing Mesh,\" and \"Deep-Shaft Extraction Nodes,\" to illustrate resource operations, and the user can interact by clicking. I'm focusing on Framer Motion and local CSS for a premium look and feel.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-26T06:34:56.884Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"t50wmtnm","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/app/platforms/oremesh/page.tsx","new_text":"\"use client\";\n\nimport { useState } from \"react\";\nimport { \n  Activity, \n  Cpu, \n  Network, \n  Server, \n  Database, \n  Zap, \n  MapPin, \n  CheckCircle, \n  Sliders, \n  MessageSquare, \n  Settings, \n  AlertTriangle, \n  Shield, \n  Compass\n} from \"lucide-react\";\nimport {\n  InnerPageShell,\n  InnerPageHero,\n  MotionReveal,\n  BentoGrid,\n  BentoCard,\n  Carousel,\n  RelatedPagesGrid,\n  PremiumCTA\n} from \"@/components/inner-pages\";\n\nconst MODULES = [\n  {\n    title: \"Field Dispatch Gateway\",\n    tag: \"Edge Ingest\",\n    desc: \"Collects high-frequency sensor streams and autonomous haul route telemetry directly from the site face, even in offline-first scenarios.\",\n    metric: \"Telemetry Ingestion\"\n  },\n  {\n    title: \"Low-Bandwidth Router\",\n    tag: \"Cognitive Routing\",\n    desc: \"Uses lightweight, high-compression packet synchronization to relay complex agent search and safety inquiries through satellite links.\",\n    metric: \"90% Payload Savings\"\n  },\n  {\n    title: \"Sovereign Safety Hub\",\n    tag: \"Compliance Ledger\",\n    desc: \"Guarantees that all machinery dispatches, gas-check reports, and shift turnovers undergo local cryptographic verification before central sync.\",\n    metric: \"Immutable Logging\"\n  },\n  {\n    title: \"Geotechnical Intelligence Core\",\n    tag: \"Sub-surface Core\",\n    desc: \"Automates parsing of core-sample grade files, drill logs, and seismic records to update field maps in real-time.\",\n    metric: \"Geological Extraction\"\n  },\n  {\n    title: \"Machinery Diagnostics Parser\",\n    tag: \"Predictive Upkeep\",\n    desc: \"Scans continuous hydraulic pressure and temperature logs from loaders and excavators to auto-generate preventive maintenance logs.\",\n    metric: \"SCADA Telemetry\"\n  }\n];\n\nconst AGENT_CARDS = [\n  {\n    title: \"Field Operations Agent\",\n    tag: \"Task Coordinator\",\n    desc: \"Unifies work orders, matches haul truck routes to shovel capacity, and coordinates shift transitions securely without human oversight.\"\n  },\n  {\n    title: \"Safety Knowledge Agent\",\n    tag: \"Regulatory Oracle\",\n    desc: \"Answers complex mining compliance queries, retrieves local ventilation formulas, and formats safety checklists over offline storage vectors.\"\n  },\n  {\n    title: \"Executive Visibility Dashboard\",\n    tag: \"Centralized Audit\",\n    desc: \"Aggregates ore grade estimates, machine downtime reports, and site incident lists into a single secure enterprise telemetry screen.\"\n  }\n];\n\nconst RELATED_LINKS = [\n  {\n    title: \"Extraction & Mining Solutions\",\n    tag: \"Industry Core\",\n    desc: \"Explore how GFF's multi-agent architectures are applied across modern heavy industries.\",\n    href: \"/industries/mining\"\n  },\n  {\n    title: \"Unified Control Center\",\n    tag: \"Cockpit Console\",\n    desc: \"Enforce compliance rules, audit execution tokens, and monitor edge swarm status from one secure panel.\",\n    href: \"/platforms/control-center\"\n  },\n  {\n    title: \"Scaling Factory\",\n    tag: \"Tier 3 Platform\",\n    desc: \"Transition your verified edge meshes into global, high-throughput automated deployments.\",\n    href: \"/platforms/factory\"\n  }\n];\n\nexport default function OREMeshPlatformPage() {\n  const [activeTab, setActiveTab] = useState<\"telemetry\" | \"safety\" | \"routing\">(\"telemetry\");\n  const [selectedNode, setSelectedNode] = useState<string>(\"shaft-4\");\n  const [isSimulating, setIsSimulating] = useState(false);\n  const [simOutput, setSimOutput] = useState(\"System ready. Click on an extraction node or select a monitoring rule to trigger verification.\");\n\n  const runSimulation = (nodeId: string, type: \"telemetry\" | \"safety\" | \"routing\") => {\n    setIsSimulating(true);\n    setSimOutput(`[OREMesh] Initializing secure handshake with edge node ${nodeId.toUpperCase()}...`);\n    \n    setTimeout(() => {\n      if (type === \"telemetry\") {\n        setSimOutput(\n          `[Gateway] Node: ${nodeId.toUpperCase()}\\n` +\n          `[SCADA] Reading vibration sensor streams: 4.2mm/s (Normal)\\n` +\n          `[Telemetry] Engine Temperature: 82°C // Hydraulic Pressure: 185 bar\\n` +\n          `[OREMesh Core] All telemetry hashes verified against secure local sandbox. Status: OPTIMAL.`\n        );\n      } else if (type === \"safety\") {\n        setSimOutput(\n          `[Knowledge Engine] Analyzing shaft-air ventilation guidelines for ${nodeId.toUpperCase()}...\\n` +\n          `[Bylaws] Verifying against local mining code standard 104-D.\\n` +\n          `[Compliance] Calculated minimum air current threshold: 350 m³/min.\\n` +\n          `[OREMesh Core] Safety rules validated successfully. No anomalies flagged.`\n        );\n      } else {\n        setSimOutput(\n          `[Packet Router] Satellite link optimization triggered over low-bandwidth stream.\\n` +\n          `[Compression] Inbound payload compressed from 4.2MB to 38KB (99.1% savings).\\n` +\n          `[Routing] Handshake completed in 184ms over high-reliability carrier.\\n` +\n          `[Status] Sync complete.`\n        );\n      }\n      setIsSimulating(false);\n    }, 600);\n  };\n\n  return (\n    <InnerPageShell>\n      <InnerPageHero\n        category=\"Industrial Mesh • Edge Execution Layer\"\n        title=\"OREMesh Edge Platform\"\n        highlightedWord=\"OREMesh\"\n        description=\"A ruggedized, low-bandwidth, sovereign edge mesh engineered to coordinate multi-agent operations, machinery telemetry, and safety compliance across remote mining sites.\"\n        breadcrumbs={[{ label: \"Platforms\", href: \"/platforms\" }, { label: \"OREMesh\" }]}\n      />\n\n      <div className=\"max-w-[1795px] mx-auto px-6 lg:px-16 pb-24 space-y-20\">\n        \n        {/* Architectural Narrative */}\n        <MotionReveal className=\"grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-12 gap-8 py-10 border-y border-white/5 items-center bg-white/[0.01] px-6 rounded-2xl\">\n          <div className=\"lg:col-span-5\">\n            <span className=\"text-xs font-mono text-[#009DFF] uppercase tracking-widest font-bold\">The Offline-First Paradigm</span>\n            <h2 className=\"text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-2\">Ruggedized Edge Autonomy</h2>\n          </div>\n          <div className=\"lg:col-span-7\">\n            <p className=\"text-white/70 font-light text-sm leading-relaxed\">\n              Subterranean environments and open-pit mining operations require highly reliable infrastructure that cannot rely on constant gigabit links. OREMesh functions as a highly sandboxed, edge-native execution layer. It orchestrates local safety agents, filters machine telemetry streams, and compresses satellite synchronization payloads, guaranteeing uninterrupted decisioning even when entirely cut off from cloud servers.\n            </p>\n          </div>\n        </MotionReveal>\n\n        {/* Interactive Mesh Network Diagram & Simulator */}\n        <MotionReveal className=\"space-y-8\">\n          <div className=\"text-center max-w-2xl mx-auto\">\n            <h2 className=\"text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold text-white tracking-tight\">Interactive Low-Bandwidth Edge Simulator</h2>\n            <p className=\"text-white/50 text-xs mt-2 font-light\">\n              Select a subterranean extraction node or monitoring category below to execute edge-agent validation scripts over our virtual OREMesh topology.\n            </p>\n          </div>\n\n          <div className=\"max-w-5xl mx-auto rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-[#04060b] overflow-hidden shadow-2xl flex flex-col md:flex-row items-stretch\">\n            {/* Interactive Visual Canvas */}\n            <div className=\"flex-grow p-6 bg-black/40 border-r border-white/5 flex flex-col items-center justify-center min-h-[350px] relative\">\n              <span className=\"absolute top-4 left-4 text-[9px] font-mono text-white/30 tracking-widest uppercase\">OREMesh Topological Node Map</span>\n              \n              <div className=\"w-full max-w-[400px] aspect-square relative flex items-center justify-center py-6\">\n                {/* SVG connection lines */}\n                <svg className=\"absolute inset-0 w-full h-full pointer-events-none\" viewBox=\"0 0 400 400\">\n                  {/* Surface to Subsurface links */}\n                  <line x1=\"200\" y1=\"60\" x2=\"100\" y2=\"180\" stroke=\"rgba(0,157,255,0.2)\" strokeWidth=\"1.5\" strokeDasharray=\"4 4\" />\n                  <line x1=\"200\" y1=\"60\" x2=\"300\" y2=\"180\" stroke=\"rgba(0,157,255,0.2)\" strokeWidth=\"1.5\" strokeDasharray=\"4 4\" />\n                  {/* Lateral subsurface meshes */}\n                  <line x1=\"100\" y1=\"180\" x2=\"300\" y2=\"180\" stroke=\"rgba(0,157,255,0.15)\" strokeWidth=\"1\" />\n                  {/* Subsurface to Subterranean links */}\n                  <line x1=\"100\" y1=\"180\" x2=\"80\" y2=\"300\" stroke={selectedNode === \"shaft-4\" ? \"#009DFF\" : \"rgba(0,157,255,0.2)\"} strokeWidth={selectedNode === \"shaft-4\" ? \"2\" : \"1.5\"} strokeDasharray=\"3 3\" />\n                  <line x1=\"100\" y1=\"180\" x2=\"200\" y2=\"300\" stroke={selectedNode === \"haul-truck-9\" ? \"#009DFF\" : \"rgba(0,157,255,0.2)\"} strokeWidth={selectedNode === \"haul-truck-9\" ? \"2\" : \"1.5\"} strokeDasharray=\"3 3\" />\n                  <line x1=\"300\" y1=\"180\" x2=\"320\" y2=\"300\" stroke={selectedNode === \"shovel-12\" ? \"#009DFF\" : \"rgba(0,157,255,0.2)\"} strokeWidth={selectedNode === \"shovel-12\" ? \"2\" : \"1.5\"} strokeDasharray=\"3 3\" />\n                </svg>\n\n                {/* Nodes rendering */}\n                {/* Surface Master Node */}\n                <div className=\"absolute top-[30px] left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 z-10 flex flex-col items-center\">\n                  <div className=\"w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-black border border-white/20 flex items-center justify-center text-[#009DFF] shadow-lg\">\n                    <Server className=\"w-5 h-5\" />\n                  </div>\n                  <span className=\"text-[9px] font-mono font-bold text-white mt-1 uppercase\">Surface Gateway</span>\n                </div>\n\n                {/* Subsurface Router Nodes */}\n                <div className=\"absolute top-[150px] left-[70px] z-10 flex flex-col items-center\">\n                  <div className=\"w-9 h-9 rounded-lg bg-black border border-white/10 flex items-center justify-center text-white/70\">\n                    <Network className=\"w-4 h-4\" />\n                  </div>\n                  <span className=\"text-[8px] font-mono text-white/50 mt-1 uppercase\">Primary Link A</span>\n                </div>\n                <div className=\"absolute top-[150px] right-[70px] z-10 flex flex-col items-center\">\n                  <div className=\"w-9 h-9 rounded-lg bg-black border border-white/10 flex items-center justify-center text-white/70\">\n                    <Network className=\"w-4 h-4\" />\n                  </div>\n                  <span className=\"text-[8px] font-mono text-white/50 mt-1 uppercase\">Primary Link B</span>\n                </div>\n\n                {/* Deep Active Nodes */}\n                <div className=\"absolute bottom-[40px] left-[50px] z-10 flex flex-col items-center\">\n                  <button \n                    onClick={() => { setSelectedNode(\"shaft-4\"); runSimulation(\"shaft-4\", activeTab); }}\n                    className={`w-11 h-11 rounded-full border flex items-center justify-center transition-all ${selectedNode === \"shaft-4\" ? \"border-[#009DFF] bg-[#009DFF]/10 text-[#009DFF] scale-110 shadow-[0_0_15px_rgba(0,157,255,0.3)]\" : \"border-white/10 bg-black hover:border-white/30 text-white/70\"}`}\n                  >\n                    <Compass className=\"w-4.5 h-4.5\" />\n                  </button>\n                  <span className=\"text-[8px] font-mono font-bold text-white mt-1 uppercase\">Shaft #4 Node</span>\n                </div>\n\n                <div className=\"absolute bottom-[40px] left-[175px] z-10 flex flex-col items-center\">\n                  <button \n                    onClick={() => { setSelectedNode(\"haul-truck-9\"); runSimulation(\"haul-truck-9\", activeTab); }}\n                    className={`w-11 h-11 rounded-full border flex items-center justify-center transition-all ${selectedNode === \"haul-truck-9\" ? \"border-[#009DFF] bg-[#009DFF]/10 text-[#009DFF] scale-110 shadow-[0_0_15px_rgba(0,157,255,0.3)]\" : \"border-white/10 bg-black hover:border-white/30 text-white/70\"}`}\n                  >\n                    <Activity className=\"w-4.5 h-4.5\" />\n                  </button>\n                  <span className=\"text-[8px] font-mono font-bold text-white mt-1 uppercase\">Haul Truck #9</span>\n                </div>\n\n                <div className=\"absolute bottom-[40px] right-[50px] z-10 flex flex-col items-center\">\n                  <button \n                    onClick={() => { setSelectedNode(\"shovel-12\"); runSimulation(\"shovel-12\", activeTab); }}\n                    className={`w-11 h-11 rounded-full border flex items-center justify-center transition-all ${selectedNode === \"shovel-12\" ? \"border-[#009DFF] bg-[#009DFF]/10 text-[#009DFF] scale-110 shadow-[0_0_15px_rgba(0,157,255,0.3)]\" : \"border-white/10 bg-black hover:border-white/30 text-white/70\"}`}\n                  >\n                    <Cpu className=\"w-4.5 h-4.5\" />\n                  </button>\n                  <span className=\"text-[8px] font-mono font-bold text-white mt-1 uppercase\">Shovel #12 Node</span>\n                </div>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n\n            {/* Simulated Workspace Controls */}\n            <div className=\"w-full md:w-[320px] p-6 flex flex-col justify-between shrink-0\">\n              <div className=\"space-y-5\">\n                <span className=\"text-[10px] font-mono font-bold text-white/30 uppercase tracking-wider block\">Simulator Parameters</span>\n                \n                {/* Tabs to select rules */}\n                <div className=\"flex flex-col gap-2\">\n                  {[\n                    { id: \"telemetry\", label: \"Edge Telemetry\", icon: Activity, desc: \"Analyse heavy equipment vibration, temperature & pressure parameters\" },\n                    { id: \"safety\", label: \"Safety Compliance Check\", icon: Shield, desc: \"Run automated local audits against federal ventilation & structural guidelines\" },\n                    { id: \"routing\", label: \"Low-Bandwidth Optimization\", icon: Zap, desc: \"Verify compression protocols over satellite uplink pathways\" }\n                  ].map((tab) => {\n                    const Icon = tab.icon;\n                    return (\n                      <button\n                        key={tab.id}\n                        onClick={() => { setActiveTab(tab.id as any); runSimulation(selectedNode, tab.id as any); }}\n                        className={`p-3 rounded-lg text-left transition-all border flex flex-col gap-1 cursor-pointer ${\n                          activeTab === tab.id \n                            ? \"bg-[#009DFF]/10 border-[#009DFF] text-white\" \n                            : \"border-white/5 bg-white/[0.01] text-white/50 hover:text-white\"\n                        }`}\n                      >\n                        <div className=\"flex items-center gap-2\">\n                          <Icon className=\"w-4 h-4 shrink-0\" />\n                          <span className=\"text-xs font-semibold\">{tab.label}</span>\n                        </div>\n                        <p className=\"text-[10px] text-white/40 leading-normal font-light\">{tab.desc}</p>\n                      </button>\n                    );\n                  })}\n                </div>\n              </div>\n\n              {/* Console log outputs */}\n              <div className=\"mt-6 pt-5 border-t border-white/5 space-y-3\">\n                <span className=\"text-[9px] font-mono font-bold text-white/30 uppercase tracking-widest block\">OREMesh Active Controller Log</span>\n                <div className=\"p-3 rounded-lg bg-black text-[10px] font-mono text-emerald-400 border border-white/5 h-[120px] overflow-y-auto whitespace-pre-wrap leading-relaxed\">\n                  {simOutput}\n                </div>\n                <button\n                  disabled={isSimulating}\n                  onClick={() => runSimulation(selectedNode, activeTab)}\n                  className=\"w-full py-2 bg-[#009DFF] hover:bg-[#0082d6] text-black font-bold text-xs rounded transition-all active:scale-[0.98] cursor-pointer\"\n                >\n                  {isSimulating ? \"Executing Verification Protocol...\" : `Run Verification (Node: ${selectedNode.toUpperCase()})`}\n                </button>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n          </div>\n        </MotionReveal>\n\n        {/* Modular Operations Carousel */}\n        <MotionReveal className=\"space-y-6\">\n          <div className=\"text-center max-w-2xl mx-auto\">\n            <span className=\"text-xs font-mono text-[#009DFF] uppercase tracking-widest font-bold\">Industrial Modules</span>\n            <h2 className=\"text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-2\">OREMesh Modular System Components</h2>\n            <p className=\"text-white/50 text-xs mt-1.5 font-light leading-relaxed\">\n              Assemble edge operations to match your geography. Every module works autonomously locally and pushes critical state changes when satellite connectivity matches SLA.\n            </p>\n          </div>\n          <Carousel items={MODULES} />\n        </MotionReveal>\n\n        {/* Specialized Agent Grid */}\n        <MotionReveal className=\"space-y-8\">\n          <div className=\"text-center max-w-2xl mx-auto\">\n            <span className=\"text-xs font-mono text-[#009DFF] uppercase tracking-widest font-bold\">Targeted Specialists</span>\n            <h2 className=\"text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-2\">Autonomous Extraction Agents</h2>\n            <p className=\"text-white/50 text-xs mt-1.5 font-light leading-relaxed\">\n              These dedicated software nodes run locally inside standard OREMesh micro-clusters, resolving queries instantly and maintaining secure audit trails.\n            </p>\n          </div>\n\n          <div className=\"grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 max-w-6xl mx-auto\">\n            {AGENT_CARDS.map((agent) => (\n              <div \n                key={agent.title}\n                className=\"p-6 rounded-[24px] border border-white/5 bg-[#050505]/70 backdrop-blur-md flex flex-col justify-between hover:border-white/12 transition-all duration-300 group\"\n              >\n                <div>\n                  <span className=\"text-[10px] font-mono text-[#009DFF] tracking-widest uppercase font-semibold\">\n                    {agent.tag}\n                  </span>\n                  <h4 className=\"text-[18px] font-semibold text-white tracking-tight mt-3 group-hover:text-[#009DFF] transition-colors\">\n                    {agent.title}\n                  </h4>\n                  <p className=\"mt-2 text-[13px] leading-relaxed text-white/60 font-light\">\n                    {agent.desc}\n                  </p>\n                </div>\n                <div className=\"mt-6 pt-4 border-t border-white/5 flex items-center justify-between\">\n                  <span className=\"text-[10px] font-mono text-white/30 uppercase\">Status: Isolated Sandbox</span>\n                  <div className=\"w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-emerald-400\" />\n                </div>\n              </div>\n            ))}\n          </div>\n        </MotionReveal>\n\n        {/* Bento Grid: Architecture Highlights */}\n        <MotionReveal className=\"space-y-8\">\n          <div className=\"text-center max-w-2xl mx-auto\">\n            <span className=\"text-xs font-mono text-[#009DFF] uppercase tracking-widest font-bold\">Hardened Infrastructure</span>\n            <h2 className=\"text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-2\">Why Enterprise Extractors Run on OREMesh</h2>\n          </div>\n\n          <BentoGrid className=\"max-w-6xl mx-auto\">\n            <BentoCard\n              title=\"Military-Grade Local Cryptography\"\n              description=\"Every sensor ingestion telemetry file, machinery log, and supervisor request is locally signed inside the sandbox container before replication.\"\n              badge=\"Security\"\n              metric={{ value: \"AES-256\", label: \"Local Encryption\" }}\n              icon={<Shield className=\"w-6 h-6\" />}\n              glowColor=\"blue\"\n            />\n            <BentoCard\n              title=\"State Compression Engine\"\n              description=\"A custom differential syncing engine reduces metadata payloads, avoiding high carrier expenses over expensive standard satellite paths.\"\n              badge=\"Efficiency\"\n              metric={{ value: \"99.1%\", label: \"Bandwidth Compression\" }}\n              icon={<Zap className=\"w-6 h-6\" />}\n              glowColor=\"blue\"\n            />\n            <BentoCard\n              title=\"SCADA Device Mapping\"\n              description=\"Direct integration with standard mining controller layers ensures quick telemetry parsing, zero middleware, and immediate hazard detection.\"\n              badge=\"Integration\"\n              metric={{ value: \"12ms\", label: \"Anomaly Response Time\" }}\n              icon={<Activity className=\"w-6 h-6\" />}\n              glowColor=\"blue\"\n            />\n          </BentoGrid>\n        </MotionReveal>\n\n        {/* References Links */}\n        <MotionReveal className=\"border-t border-white/5 pt-12\">\n          <RelatedPagesGrid links={RELATED_LINKS} />\n        </MotionReveal>\n\n        {/* Premium CTA */}\n        <div className=\"pt-8\">\n          <PremiumCTA\n            title=\"Deploy Ruggedized Agent Intelligence to Your Extraction Sites\"\n            description=\"Consult GFF engineering specialists to configure a high-availability, offline-first OREMesh edge setup for your remote assets and subterranean networks.\"\n            primaryLabel=\"Contact GFF Systems Architects\"\n            primaryHref=\"/contact\"\n          />\n        </div>\n\n      </div>\n    </InnerPageShell>\n  );\n}"}}}
